{
  "text": "Even the mere existence of an SCD for U(b,a) is still an open problem. However to deduce the Sperner property, as well as rank unimodality, you don't quite need a symmetric chain decomposition. It is enough to have a maximal chain decomposition all whose chains pass through the largest level set. Stanley [CITATION_1] , using the \"hard Lefschetz theorem\" from algebraic geometry, proved the existence of such a chain decomposition for the poset U(b,a) as well as for some other posets, among them the posets M(n) of all strict partitions whose largest part is ≤ n:",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "17799910"
  },
